text: La Corne-en-Vexin is a commune in the Oise department in northern France. It was established on 1 January 2019 by merger of the former communes of Énencourt-le-Sec (the seat), Boissy-le-Bois and Hardivillers-en-Vexin.Arrêté préfectoral 28 September 2018 and 14 December 2018 ==See also== * Communes of the Oise department ==References== Category:Communes of Oise Category:Populated places established in 2019
title: La Corne-en-Vexin
